highlights.description: I've had trouble finding an affordable place to live....I'm always worried about ending up on the street
Portions of Madison are far angrier than any of us have come face to face with
Maybe a conversation with more disagreement and diversity
How will I know if I am quoted and if they got it right?
People are hustling to live month to month.... disposability of people (workers)
We should be paying more for food.. for farmers... but we want everything cheap... but people have to spend 80% of their income on housing... it should be a human right.
There is a greater urgency to push certain issues by certain communities.  Some are angrier than others.
Speaks to his own assumptions about marginalized people and internal conflict of what might be racist thoughts from time to time.  Attributes some of these thoughts/reactions to upbringing.
Institutional racism and the disparities on educational outcomes.
Disparities at the intersection of race and class in Madison.  People rarely talk about these issues.
POC still face racial disparities even in light reaching a higher socio-economic status.
There needs to be more representation on elected boards in Madison, specifically the school board.
Does not necessarily agree with every demand offered by YBG, but is willing to listen to understand.
calling the police on homeless people
